line_1: And GET you too — was, saith! no boyish feat.
line_2: That we should ask you to our medley treat,

line_1: I'll in, and swear to Hal — I've done the feat.
line_2: So — be but kind, and countenance the cheat,

line_1: Flock ev'ry Sunday to the feat,
line_2: To stare about them, and to eat.

line_1: O native isle, fair Freedom's happiest feat!
line_2: At thought of thee my bounding pulses beat;
' Hung on these Shelves, the Muses Seat.
